V1.0 

Initial Release 

	DESCRIPTION:

		Allows user to send commands to a remote Terminal and Have it Executed and displayed on the
		remote host.
		EXAMPLE:  There is a remote Terminal running on a machine to which you only have SSH access
		and you want to display HTOP in the Terminal to show the Machines performance stats.

		USAGE:   $ sudo ttyx [ -n (new line after cmd)] [DEVICE] [COMMAND]

		WORKING EXAMPLE: $ sudo ttyx -n /dev/tty1 htop

INSTALLATION:

		git clone https://github.com/D31337m3/ttyx.git 

		make

		sudo cp ttyx ./bin 

